68
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:45,389
SPEAKER_22: What are you crying for?

69
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:49,490
SPEAKER_22: If nothing else, can't you think of the baby?

269
00:30:44,769 --> 00:30:46,170
SPEAKER_22: As for me...

270
00:30:46,900 --> 00:30:50,569
SPEAKER_22: I want to live. There's nothing like family.

288
00:32:40,819 --> 00:32:42,279
SPEAKER_22: Which corpses?

349
00:44:46,679 --> 00:44:48,010
SPEAKER_22: The day...

355
00:45:13,739 --> 00:45:15,260
SPEAKER_22: Written?

356
00:45:15,340 --> 00:45:19,000
SPEAKER_22: I never thought I'd make it back alive.

388
00:47:24,369 --> 00:47:27,559
SPEAKER_22: He joined the army as a driver.
